: 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloom_(2003_film)\", \"score\": 0.6869339278925753, \"rank\": 0.1432835820895115, \"text\": \"Bloom\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloom_(2003_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloom_(2003_film)\"}, {\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daley Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 410, \"end\": 418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mo Farah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9998974555935756, \"rank\": 8.948865083766338e-05, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daley Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9658450438762797, \"rank\": 0.035362168571538656, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.6004492896661643e-12, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a reason\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 324}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 353}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"their tracks\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 434}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"his remarkable life\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"career\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"a short piece\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"little resemblance\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"the man\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is taken from the 1976 MontrealOlympics, at the start of the second day of what was only his fifth seniordecathlon.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1976 MontrealOlympics\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"the second day\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"only his fifth seniordecathlon\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Already languishing well down the field overnight, he begins the morning with a truly atrocious 110-metre hurdle race that sees him whack every obstacle in his path and trail in a distant last place.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"a truly atrocious 110-metre hurdle race\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"every obstacle\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"his path\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"trail\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"a distant last place\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a dreadful performance.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a dreadful performance\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end of the 10-discipline competition, Thompson would end up 18th of 23 finishers.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1082}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10-discipline competition\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"18th\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"23 finishers\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was 18th on my 18th birthday, so very chuffed,\\\" he recalls, onDaley: Olympic Superstar.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1251, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my 18th birthday\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1192}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Superstar\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson was not there to win; he knew he stood no chance, explaining that \\\"it was so, so exciting because nothing was expected of me\\\".\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no chance\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, he vowed to absorb every snippet of information he could, seizing the opportunity to learn.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every snippet\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"information\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, in between his runs, jumps and throws, he set about pestering America's eventualOlympic champion Bruce - now Caitlyn - Jenner.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2457654781515234e-19, \"text\": \"Jenner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his runs\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"throws\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"America's eventualOlympic champion\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"Bruce\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would just go up to him and ask questions,\\\" says Thompson.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How much do you train?\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where do you train?\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jenner was fantastic, giving me all the information that I needed to get to the next step.\\\"\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1728, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2457654781515234e-19, \"text\": \"Jenner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the information\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"the next step\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jenner's victory that day came courtesy of a world-record points tally that would stand for almost four years until Thompson surpassed it.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2457654781515234e-19, \"text\": \"Jenner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlyn_Jenner\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"courtesy\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"a world-record points tally\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"almost four years\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end of his career, Thompson would win two Olympic, one world, two European and three Commonwealth titles.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.040221628227737e-16, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"two Olympic\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"one world\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He would set four world records and go unbeaten in the decathlon for an astonishing nine years.\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four world records\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"the decathlon\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2137}, {\"ngram\": \"an astonishing nine years\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Montreal Olympics were formative in creating a true British sporting great.\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1976_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.84025144847413e-22, \"text\": \"Montreal Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1976_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1976_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2226, \"end\": 2233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet if things were then as they are now, he would never even have been given the chance to compete there.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2263}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2337}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were few surprises whenTeam GBannounced their athletics squad for the upcomingParis Olympics, and it did little to detract from the controversy the lineup caused and is continuing to cause.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"few surprises\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"GBannounced\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletics squad\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"the upcomingParis Olympics\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversy\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"the lineup\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sticking resolutely to its policy of only picking athletes it deems capable of top-eight finishes, UK Athletics - the sport's national governing body, which selects the team for international events - has opted to reject a host of invites for athletes who had otherwise qualified through their world ranking.\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2652, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Athletics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its policy\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2586}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"top-eight finishes\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's national governing body\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2726}, {\"ngram\": \"international events\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2751}, {\"ngram\": \"a host\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"invites\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2791}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision, understandably, has prompted fury from some whose Olympic dreams have been dashed, of whom there were at least half a dozen.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The decision\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2875}, {\"ngram\": \"fury\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"whose Olympic dreams\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"at least half a dozen\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 3000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them was discus throwerJade Lally, whose best mark this year is the furthest by a British woman since the early 1980s and would have been good enough for seventh at the last Olympics.\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3090, \"end\": 3097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"discus\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3023}, {\"ngram\": \"whose best mark\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3058}, {\"ngram\": \"the early 1980s\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3125}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Olympics\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She toldThe Telegraphshe is now planning to retire from the sport, adding: \\\"If you are a British athlete, and have already missed out on a championship, I would 100 per cent encourage anybody to switch to another country if that is an option.\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3282, \"end\": 3289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Telegraphshe\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3217}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3258}, {\"ngram\": \"a championship\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3344}, {\"ngram\": \"anybody\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3384}, {\"ngram\": \"another country\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3413}, {\"ngram\": \"an option\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like I have wasted a career trying to prove a federation wrong.\\\"\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a career\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was hammer throwerAnna Purchase, who has reached world and European finals over the past year, and her male compatriots Jake Norris and Kenneth Ikeji, whose best efforts this season would have placed them seventh and eighth respectively at the 2020Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 3509, \"to\": 3775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3635, \"end\": 3639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"score\": 0.9999999789101823, \"rank\": 2.1089079845482523e-08, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\"}, {\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lando_Norris\", \"score\": 0.9987801334613721, \"rank\": 0.0006955802744694476, \"text\": \"Norris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lando_Norris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lando_Norris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hammer throwerAnna Purchase\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3546}, {\"ngram\": \"world and European finals\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3589}, {\"ngram\": \"the past year\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"her male compatriots\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3634}, {\"ngram\": \"Kenneth Ikeji\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3664}, {\"ngram\": \"whose best efforts\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3684}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"British shot-put champion Amelia Campbell, another athlete snubbed, called UK Athletics' policy \\\"disgusting\\\" and said it was \\\"killing\\\" the sport in Britain.\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3776, \"end\": 3783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3802, \"end\": 3817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amelia_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amelia Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amelia_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amelia_Campbell\"}, {\"begin\": 3851, \"end\": 3863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Athletics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 3924, \"end\": 3931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9658450438762797, \"rank\": 0.035362168571538656, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 3911, \"to\": 3920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, what is going on?\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While no one from the federation has fielded media questions since the Olympic team announcement earlier this month, UK Athletics chair Ian Beattie did write a piece on theAthletics Weeklywebsite in an attempt toexplain the logic.\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 4186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4073, \"end\": 4085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Athletics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 4092, \"end\": 4103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Beattie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ian Beattie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Beattie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Beattie\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 3962, \"to\": 3968}, {\"ngram\": \"the federation\", \"from\": 3974, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"media questions\", \"from\": 4001, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic team announcement\", \"from\": 4023, \"to\": 4052}, {\"ngram\": \"a piece\", \"from\": 4114, \"to\": 4121}, {\"ngram\": \"theAthletics Weeklywebsite\", \"from\": 4125, \"to\": 4151}, {\"ngram\": \"an attempt\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4165}, {\"ngram\": \"the logic\", \"from\": 4176, \"to\": 4185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of his claims were staggering to many observers.\", \"from\": 4187, \"to\": 4240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his claims\", \"from\": 4195, \"to\": 4205}, {\"ngram\": \"many observers\", \"from\": 4225, \"to\": 4239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"An athlete getting to the Olympics with little chance of qualifying from their heat or pool does not have a significant impact on inspiring the nation, and therefore does not merit public funding,\\\" he wrote.\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An athlete\", \"from\": 4243, \"to\": 4253}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4265, \"to\": 4277}, {\"ngram\": \"little chance\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4296}, {\"ngram\": \"their heat\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4326}, {\"ngram\": \"pool\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4334}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant impact\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4369}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4393}, {\"ngram\": \"public funding\", \"from\": 4424, \"to\": 4438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is also an issue that larger teams can dilute the level of support given during the championships to our genuine medal contenders, and that there is a demotivational effect on the team as a whole when the first few days of the championship are dominated by athletes failing to qualify from their heat or pool.\\\"\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4769, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 4467, \"to\": 4475}, {\"ngram\": \"larger teams\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4493}, {\"ngram\": \"the level\", \"from\": 4505, \"to\": 4514}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 4518, \"to\": 4525}, {\"ngram\": \"the championships\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4556}, {\"ngram\": \"our genuine medal contenders\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4588}, {\"ngram\": \"a demotivational effect\", \"from\": 4608, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4643}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole\", \"from\": 4647, \"to\": 4654}, {\"ngram\": \"the first few days\", \"from\": 4660, \"to\": 4678}, {\"ngram\": \"the championship\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4698}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4716, \"to\": 4724}, {\"ngram\": \"their heat\", \"from\": 4749, \"to\": 4759}, {\"ngram\": \"pool\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If what he says is true, then Thompson's 18th-place finish at the 1976 Olympics was nothing but a hindrance.\", \"from\": 4771, \"to\": 4879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4801, \"end\": 4809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9945784835285224, \"rank\": 0.005451069534804722, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1976 Olympics\", \"from\": 4833, \"to\": 4850}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4862}, {\"ngram\": \"a hindrance\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Triple jump world record holder Jonathan Edwards must have sucked the energy out of his British teammates when he finished 23rd in 1988 and 35th in 1992 - irrespective of him then going on to win silver and gold at the next two Olympics.\", \"from\": 4880, \"to\": 5117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4912, \"end\": 4928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Edwards_(theologian)\", \"score\": 0.9098235446550247, \"rank\": 0.05189732142857242, \"text\": \"Jonathan Edwards\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Edwards_(theologian)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Edwards_(theologian)\"}, {\"begin\": 4968, \"end\": 4975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the energy\", \"from\": 4946, \"to\": 4956}, {\"ngram\": \"35th\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5024}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 5076, \"to\": 5082}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 5087, \"to\": 5091}, {\"ngram\": \"the next two Olympics\", \"from\": 5095, \"to\": 5116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are any number of other examples of British Olympic also-rans converting into world-beaters a few years later who have made their country proud.\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5161, \"end\": 5168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9721789442531585, \"rank\": 0.01892202448363756, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any number\", \"from\": 5129, \"to\": 5139}, {\"ngram\": \"other examples\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5157}, {\"ngram\": \"world-beaters\", \"from\": 5203, \"to\": 5216}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 5249, \"to\": 5262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Javelin throwerTessa Sandersonfinished 10th and 19th at the Olympics before she finally won gold in 1984.Sir Mo Farahdid not advance from his 5,000m heat at the 2008 Games but then went on to claim four Olympic and six world titles.\", \"from\": 5270, \"to\": 5502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5375, \"end\": 5381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Mo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_(wrestler)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Javelin\", \"from\": 5270, \"to\": 5277}, {\"ngram\": \"Sandersonfinished 10th\", \"from\": 5291, \"to\": 5313}, {\"ngram\": \"19th\", \"from\": 5318, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5338}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 5362, \"to\": 5366}, {\"ngram\": \"his 5,000m heat\", \"from\": 5408, \"to\": 5423}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2008 Games\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5441}, {\"ngram\": \"four Olympic and six world titles\", \"from\": 5468, \"to\": 5501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both athletes went on to become feted national treasures whose names we may not have even been aware of in another time with a different policy in place.\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both athletes\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5516}, {\"ngram\": \"feted national treasures\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5559}, {\"ngram\": \"whose names\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5571}, {\"ngram\": \"another time\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"a different policy\", \"from\": 5628, \"to\": 5646}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 5650, \"to\": 5655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not difficult to speculate about the overriding reason behind such a short-sighted selection policy.\", \"from\": 5658, \"to\": 5764, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the overriding reason\", \"from\": 5697, \"to\": 5718}, {\"ngram\": \"such a short-sighted selection policy\", \"from\": 5726, \"to\": 5763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only last December, Beattie was having to offer reassurances that UK Athletics would stay afloat after announcing record losses of \\u00a33.7m for a financial year in which it failed to secure a title sponsor or television deal.\", \"from\": 5765, \"to\": 5987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5831, \"end\": 5843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Athletics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Beattie\", \"from\": 5785, \"to\": 5792}, {\"ngram\": \"reassurances\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5825}, {\"ngram\": \"record losses\", \"from\": 5879, \"to\": 5892}, {\"ngram\": \"a financial year\", \"from\": 5906, \"to\": 5922}, {\"ngram\": \"a title sponsor\", \"from\": 5952, \"to\": 5967}, {\"ngram\": \"television deal\", \"from\": 5971, \"to\": 5986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A further seven-figure loss is projected for its next accounting year.\", \"from\": 5988, \"to\": 6058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A further seven-figure loss\", \"from\": 5988, \"to\": 6015}, {\"ngram\": \"its next accounting year\", \"from\": 6033, \"to\": 6057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hence theTeam GBathletics contingent for these Paris Games is the smallest at any Olympics for 20 years, while the places turned down by the federation instead go to lesser-performing rivals from other nations.\", \"from\": 6060, \"to\": 6270, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"GBathletics contingent\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6096}, {\"ngram\": \"these Paris Games\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6118}, {\"ngram\": \"any Olympics\", \"from\": 6138, \"to\": 6150}, {\"ngram\": \"20 years\", \"from\": 6155, \"to\": 6163}, {\"ngram\": \"the places\", \"from\": 6171, \"to\": 6181}, {\"ngram\": \"the federation\", \"from\": 6197, \"to\": 6211}, {\"ngram\": \"lesser-performing rivals\", \"from\": 6226, \"to\": 6250}, {\"ngram\": \"other nations\", \"from\": 6256, \"to\": 6269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not Sweden, though.\", \"from\": 6271, \"to\": 6290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6275, \"end\": 6281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.7304197606158498, \"rank\": 0.3221020352333821, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This week, five of the nine Swedish track and field athletes whose Olympic invitations were similarly turned down by their national federation began crowdfunding to start legal proceedings against the decision.\", \"from\": 6292, \"to\": 6502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6320, \"end\": 6327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9999884487605005, \"rank\": 1.1526824608866949e-05, \"text\": \"Swedish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}], \"no